    Fix stale-message guard dropping all intermediate steps (chatThinking)

    The parent_id on SYSTEM_INTERMEDIATE messages is set by NAT's
    get_intermediate_step_parent_id(), which returns an internal step/LLM
    call ID -- not the user message ID stored in activeParentId. The
    parent_id correlation therefore never matched, causing every thinking
    step to be discarded as 'stale' and chatThinking to disappear entirely.

    Fix: remove parent_id correlation from onIntermediateStep. Replace it
    with the same isStreaming guard used for isFinal: if the store is not
    currently streaming, the workflow that produced the step was already
    cancelled/disconnected and the step should be dropped.

    The parent_id correlation is kept only for SYSTEM_RESPONSE messages,
    where NAT reliably uses self._message_parent_id (the client message ID).

    Update tests to set mockStoreState.isStreaming = true before firing
    intermediate-step callbacks so the guard behaves as expected.

